          "text": "Base directory for this skill: /home/leon0399/.claude/skills/octocat\n\n# GitHub Skill\n\nUse the `gh` CLI for all GitHub interactions. Never suggest the web UI when `gh` can do it.\n\n## Pull Requests\n\nCreate a PR with a multi-line body (the `--body` flag mangles `\\n` into literal characters — always use `--body-file`):\n\n```bash\ncat > /tmp/pr-body.md << 'EOF'\n## Summary\nDescription here.\nEOF\ngh pr create --base main --head <branch> --title \"<title>\" --body-file /tmp/pr-body.md\n```\n\nIf you must use inline text, use shell ANSI-C quoting: `--body $'line1\\n\\nline2'`\n\nCheck CI status:\n```bash\ngh pr checks <number>\n```\n\nView a PR with specific fields:\n```bash\ngh pr view <number> --json title,state,reviews,statusCheckRollup\n```\n\nCheckout a PR locally:\n```bash\ngh pr checkout 123\n```\n\nView PR diff:\n```bash\ngh pr diff 123\ngh pr diff 123 --name-only  # file list only\n```\n\nMerge a PR:\n```bash\ngh pr merge 123 --squash --delete-branch   # squash merge + cleanup\ngh pr merge 123 --rebase --delete-branch   # rebase merge + cleanup\n```\n\nEdit PR metadata:\n```bash\ngh pr edit 123 --title \"New title\" --add-label bug --add-reviewer user1\n```\n\n## CI / GitHub Actions\n\nList recent workflow runs:\n```bash\ngh run list --limit 10\n```\n\nView a failed run and its logs:\n```bash\ngh run view <run-id>\ngh run view <run-id> --log-failed\n```\n\nWatch a run until it completes (use `--exit-status` to get non-zero exit on failure):\n```bash\ngh run watch <run-id> --exit-status\n```\n\n## PR Reviews\n\n### Fetching review threads\n\nUse the bundled `pr-reviews` skill/script for fetching review threads — it handles GraphQL pagination and flattens the response. If `pr-reviews` is unavailable, use the GraphQL query below.\n\nThe REST API (`/pulls/{number}/comments`) does **not** expose `isResolved` — you need GraphQL for resolution status. This is why models often get review fetching wrong: they try REST and miss critical fields.